                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Dream run for home team
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, May 27: Vodafone has reported a 14.1 per cent jump in revenue to 35.5 billion, with its India business delivering a strong growth of over 50 per cent for the year ended March 31, 2008.        
	The group posted a 14.1 per cent increase in revenues with an organic growth of 4.2 per cent for the year ended March 31, a company statement said.         
	Vodafones adjusted operating profit increased 5.7 per cent to 10.1 billion, while its earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortisation grew 10.2 per cent to 13.2 billion in 2007-08.        
	Under the leadership of CEO Arun Sarin, Vodafone had registered strong growth during the year in eastern Europe, West Asia, Africa and the Asia-Pacific.        
	The groups revenues from these regions grew 45.1 per cent during the year ended March 31, reflecting acquisitions in India and Turkey. In India, the group has over 44 million customers. In its outlook for the current financial year, the group expects revenues to be around 40 billion.         
	He (Sarin) is an excellent person to deal with. He has added a lot of value to our partnership, an official at Vodafone Essar said.        
	Analysts said the Indian companys results reflected its successful integration into the Vodafone group.         
	Over the last year, Vodafone has displaced BSNL to become the third largest operator in India. This was also helped by a slump in BSNLs business around May last year, said Harit Shah, telecom analyst at Angel Broking.                                                                                                                                      
